morphospeciesIDRemarks: Stem glabrous green 4-angled and grooved; branching from leaf axils. Petioles purple and pubescent with stiff hairs. Leaves widest at base and cordate to uneven; tapering evenly to an acute tip. Margins serrate to slightly doubly serrate. Venation mainly arching; netted between; appear to be around 14 lateral veins per leaf. Leaves sparsely pubescent both above and below; underside is paler but not glaucous.
